{"title": "Fluorescent Footprints", "content": "Rather than track by means of conventional detective skills, the character uses something akin to Aura Vision to track the footsteps of their prey. Even on surfaces or terrain that would never show their passing otherwise, or where their tracks would disappear into those of a crowd. The Empath may even be able to tell the emotional and physical condition of the person being tracked by the color of their footprints.\n\nRobots and characters/animals with Super Senses can get in on this too by using infrared sight to track the heat left in their prey's footsteps. Here the downside is that in extremely hot environments it's useless, or if too much time passes.\n\nThis is usually because of the Rule of Perception: if the trail didn't light up, it wouldn't be visible to the audience. The Scarily Competent Tracker usually has their tracking and/or Super Senses depicted this way.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FluorescentFootprints", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PsiOpsTheMindgateConspiracy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLordOfTheRings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Madagascar3EuropesMostWanted", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TRONLegacy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ShortCircuit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/V1983", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheManFromUncle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BurnNotice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AssassinsCreedII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AssassinsCreedBrotherHood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamAsylum", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HeavyRain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MetalGear", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MetalGearSolid4", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PsiOpsTheMindgateConspiracy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheJourneymanProject", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DragonQuestVII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MountAndBlade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Doom", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/